{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>ABC transporters belong to the ATP-Binding Cassette (ABC) superfamily, which uses the hydrolysis of ATP to energise diverse biological systems. ABC transporters minimally consist of two conserved regions: a highly conserved ATP binding cassette (ABC) and a less conserved transmembrane domain (TMD). These can be found on the same protein or on two different ones. Most ABC transporters function as a dimer and therefore are constituted of four domains, two ABC modules and two TMDs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This entry consists of nodulation protein J (Nod J). Nod J together with NodI ([interpro:IPR005978]), forms a membrane transport complex involved in the nodulation process [[cite:PUB00062334], [cite:PUB00062335], [cite:PUB00035597]]. It exports lipo-chitin oligosaccharides that induce nodule formation in the host plant [[cite:PUB00034686], [cite:PUB00003841]]. The substrates transported by the non-rhizobial proteins are not currently known.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR01291" "ABC-2 type transporter, NodJ family"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "ABC-2 type transporter, NodJ", "short" "ABC_transptNodJ"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 323, "taxa" 1657, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1779, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1779, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1427}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR005981", :literature {"PUB00034686" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Cardenas L" "Dominguez J" "Santana O" "Quinto C."], "ISO_journal" "Gene", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0378-1119(96)00166-7", "medline_journal" "Gene", "title" "The role of the nodI and nodJ genes in the transport of Nod metabolites in Rhizobium etli.", "year" 1996, "raw_pages" "18